cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with language modeling and sentence ordering. It could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it uses LSTM models for language modeling. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it deals with natural language processing tasks. It may also fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it uses neural networks for language modeling. Finally, it could be categorized under cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) as it uses beam search algorithms for sentence ordering.
